title: Introduction to Computer Science
course_details: This course is an introduction to the fundamental principles of computer science. It covers topics such as algorithms, data structures, programming languages, software engineering, and computer hardware. Students will gain an understanding of how computers work and how they can be used to solve problems.
course_keywords: programming fundamentals, data structures and algorithms, ethics of computer science, problem solving

title: Introduction to Mechanical Engineering
course_details: This course provides an overview of mechanical engineering and its role in solving real-world problems. The course covers the fundamental principles of mechanics, thermodynamics, and materials science. Students will learn how to apply these principles to design and analyze mechanical systems.
course_keywords: statics and dynamics, mechanics, energy and motion equilibrium, thermodynamics, manufacturing

title: Introduction to Electrical Engineering
course_details: This course introduces the principles of electrical engineering, including circuit analysis, electromagnetism, and electronics. Students will learn about electric power systems, signals and systems, and digital signal processing. The course provides hands-on experience in designing and building electrical circuits and systems.
course_keywords: circuits, electromagnetism, electronics, digital signal processing, power systems

title: Introduction to Chemical Engineering
course_details: This course provides an overview of chemical engineering and its role in solving real-world problems. The course covers the fundamental principles of chemical reactions, thermodynamics, mass and energy balance, and transport phenomena. Students will learn how to apply these principles to design and analyze chemical processes and systems.
course_keywords: chemical reactions, thermodynamics, mass balance, energy balance, transport phenomena

title: Introduction to Civil Engineering
course_details: This course provides an introduction to the fundamental principles of civil engineering, including the design and construction of structures, transportation systems, and water resources. Students will learn about the materials and methods used in civil engineering, and gain an understanding of how these principles are applied in real-world projects.
course_keywords: structural engineering, transportation engineering, water resources, construction materials, infrastructure design

title: Project Management
course_details: This course provides an overview of project management and its role in successful completion of projects. Students will learn about project planning, scheduling, budgeting, risk management, and quality control. The course will also cover project leadership, team management, communication, and stakeholder management.
course_keywords: project planning, scheduling, budgeting, risk management, quality control, project leadership, team management, communication, stakeholder management

title: Introduction to Material Science
course_details: This course provides an overview of material science and its role in designing and engineering materials for various applications. Students will learn about the structure and properties of materials, such as metals, ceramics, polymers, and composites. The course will cover different methods for processing and synthesizing materials, and the techniques for characterizing their properties.
course_keywords: structure and properties of materials, metals, ceramics, polymers, composites, processing and synthesizing materials, techniques for characterizing properties

title: Introduction to Nuclear Engineering
course_details: This course provides an introduction to nuclear engineering and its role in various industries, including energy generation and medical applications. Students will learn about the basic principles of nuclear physics, reactor design, radiation protection, and nuclear fuel cycles. The course will also cover the current trends and future prospects of nuclear technology.
course_keywords: nuclear physics, reactor design, radiation protection, nuclear fuel cycles, nuclear energy, medical applications
